caption: Quite a detailed column to recognise a famous Polish poet and writer. As profound as some of his works.

Monument to Adam Mickiewicz. Born in Belarus near Novogrudok. Belarusians, Poles and Lithuanians consider him their poet. And in these countries his works are studied in schools. Such a controversial personality. Even though he was born in Belarus, he wrote in Polish. A person who influenced the culture of these countries and is recognized in Europe deserves to be immortalized. Good luck to all.

He lived in Poland for a long time, the Poles love this poet very much. And in Belarus they also consider him one of their own. It was nice to see monuments to him in Paris. Although this is not surprising, he lived here and even taught...
Adam Bernard Mickiewicz, is considered the most important of the Three Bards of Polish Romanticism in a time of non-existence of a Polish nation state and as the national poet of Poland.

It's nice to come across a Polish accent while walking around Paris.
